Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Back of a length and on off, this is defended.
Inside edge! This is outside off and it is on a length. Burns looks to go hard at it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On the middle pole, Burns works it to mid-wicket.
A good short one, Burns ducks under it at the very end.
Outside off, the batter lets it be.
A dot to end! Short and on middle, this is kept out.
Fuller and on middle, Root hits it to mid on.
This is on middle, it is worked to short leg.
Floats it up on off, Root lunges and keeps it out.
FOUR! 100 up for England! This is on the pads, Root goes back and works it fine, it races past short fine leg and to the fence.
A couple now! Nicely played! Lyon floats it up on off, Root strokes it back past the bowler and collects a brace.
That stays low but it is down the leg side, Root looks to flick but misses.
Good length around off, Burns strokes it on the up to covers.
This is angled into the batter who works it to square leg.
Around off again, Burns strokes it back to the bowler. Siddle is just not getting anything off the surface. He is keeping it tight but Australia need a wicket.

FOUR! Edgy! When he does create something, it does not go to hand. It has just not been Australia's day till now. Siddle goes full and outside off, Burns flashes at it. The ball goes off the outside edge over and just wide of the fourth slip fielder and into the third man fence.
This is angled into the batter, he works it to mid-wicket.
This is bowled just outside off, Burns lets it be.
Around the off pole, Root guides it to point.
FOUR! Brilliant shot! Pattinson angles this into the pads, trying to hit Root in front. Joe gets his bat down in time and works it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
England are off Nelson as Root works it down to fine leg for one.
On the fuller side and on off, Burns pushes it back to the bowler who makes a half-stop but no runs conceded.
Squares him up but runs for the batter! This is on off and it straightens. Burns looks to defend but it goes off the outer half through backward point and the batters take two.

FOUR! This is frustrating, very frustrating for Australia. They had a fourth slip all this while, they move that fielder to the gully position and it goes through the former position. Fuller and around off, Burns goes after it but the ball flies off the outside edge down to the third man fence. Runs coming thick and fast for England now. They trail by 166.
Fuller and on middle, Root hits it to mid on.
Back of a length and on off, Root defends it onto the ground.
Continues bowling it on off and on a back of a length. Root is once again solid in defense.

FOUR! Another one off the edge! Cummins goes fuller and outside off, Root looks to drive but it goes off the outside edge past point and into the third man fence. 100-run stand up between the two. They are laying the platform for England to take a good lead here.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the batter, Root works it to mid-wicket.
The last ball is left alone as it is outside off.
On a good length and around off, this is kept out.
Down the leg side, the batter looks to flick but misses. Paine fails to collect it cleanly but no runs taken.
Outside off now, Burns lets it be.
One more leave as another delivery is bowled outside off.
From around the wicket angles this one into the pads, Burns works it through mid-wicket for one.
Another single as Root works it to fine leg.
Close again! Cummins lands this on off and gets it to jag back in a little. Root tries to defend but it hits the inside edge and then hits the pads.
Back of a length on off, Root guides it to gully.
Goes fuller this time, Root strokes it back to mid off.
Back of a length and on off, this is kept out towards cover for one.

EDGED AND FOUR! Australia can only smile about it! This is fuller and around off, it is angling away. Burns looks to drive but it goes off the outside edge through the slip cordon and down to the third man fence.
FOUR! This is right off the middle! On a good length and around off, Burns pushes it back past mid off. Wade runs after it and slides but his effort goes in vain.
On the fuller side again, Root strokes it to mid off.
This is angled into the batter, Root works it to mid on.
On middle, Root plays it with a straight bat to mid off.
Shorter and outside off, Root hops and guides it towards point for one.
Full again and on off, Burns jams it out to square leg.
BEATEN! This is on off, it is angled away. Burns looks to defend but is beaten.
Short but angling into the batsman who is squared up to the rising delivery, the edge flies off past a diving Khawaja and races towards fence but fielder chases and keeps it to three.
Landed around off, Burns looks to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Good delivery again, shorter in length, this one leaves the batsman who has a prod at it but is beaten.
A bouncer on middle, ducked under.
This was a quicker one from Cummins but wide of  off stump, Burns shoulders arms to this one.
Similar line from Cummins and Burns is not bothered about it.
Around middle and off, on a length, tucked through square leg for a single.
Shorter length from Pattinson but is on middle and off, Burns stands tall and defends well.
This was wide, bit of room for Burns to bring his drive, times it well towards cover to take one.
FOUR! Another edge that goes between the slips and gully. Root moves to 49 with this lucky boundary. The ball was on a perfect length, asking the batsman to drive.

50 for Root! Or maybe not. The crowd cheers, thinking he has got to that landmark but then quietens on seeing the umpire raise his leg to signal a leg bye. On a length around middle and off, coming in, Joe misses his flick and is hit on the pads. The ball deflects off his pads towards mid-wicket and a leg bye is taken.
Another shorter length, angling away, Burns blocks it easily.
On the hips of Root who clips it fine to reach his half-century, 42nd half-century for the England skipper. The delivery was shorter on length, angling away. Bread and Butter for Root, that delivery.

Ouch. That has hurt. On a length outside off, Root looks to defend but the ball nips back in and hits him on the inner half of his right thigh. Cummins appeals for LBW but the impact was well outside off. Root takes some time to get used to the pain...
Shorter length, Root leans forward and blocks well. Looking solid as ever.
Outside off, Root taps it towards point and sets off for a single. Usman Khawaja has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Had he hit, Burns was a goner. Now, they take the overthrow as well.
Shorter on length again, guides it through to point and hares back for a couple.
Similar line but coming into the batsman who hangs in the crease to block this back to the bowler.
Fuller length, on the middle-stump, Burns pushes it to the fielder easily.
Around middle and off, pushed towards mid-wicket.
There's a bit of turn from the middle, Burns goes back for a punch, finds the cover fielder.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
On the shorter length but on the stumps, Burns pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Burns looks to defend but the ball stays low and beats the outside edge. Paine cannot collect and concedes a bye.
Fuller length but on the off stump, Burns leans forward for a cover drive, gets beaten.
Down the leg side, Burns looks to tuck but the ball goes off his pads towards fine leg. A leg bye taken.
Looking for the yorker as Siddle goes full, Root negates safely.
Played to the point region by the batsman.
Full again but angling into the batsman, Root whips it perfectly using the angle but straight to mid-wicket.

OUT! Stunning caught and bowled! At last, at long last, at long long last, Australia get a wicket. After toiling for hours, with edges not going to hand, Siddle has struck. Full and around off, Root drives this straight back, but does not bother to keep it down. That is a good shot alright, but Siddle sticks out his right hand and voila - it sticks! Root cannot believe his luck. For once, something goes Australia's way and the 132-run stand is broken. Root departs for 57 and the deficit is now 130.
On the good length, Burns stays in his crease to block it comfortably of his front foot.
Outside off, punched back to the bowler.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
That nipped away. Super delivery, slightly quicker. Pitches and goes away to beat the outside edge of the left-hander. Burns looked to push that to the off side.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! That is a bad ball to finish the over. Short and outside off, Burns rocks back, picks the length in a trice and punches it through the covers. The deficit is now 126.
Full and around off, flicked away but straight to short mid-wicket.
Short on the off side, Denly has a confident block to this fifth stump line delivery.
Targets the stumps this time but this is a half volley, Denly gets off the mark with a whip off his legs, takes a couple.
This was close to the off-stump line, Denly leans forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Fifth stump line, the ball pitches and goes away, too wide for Denly to try anything on that one.
Straight one this time on the off stump line, pushes it back to the bowler again.
Fuller length from Lyon, Burns pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and around off, pushed towards point for a single.
Shorter in length, Denly pushes it towards mid on, Lyon goes and fields the ball.
Around off, solidly blocked out.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid on.
On the middle stump, fuller in length, Denly times this well but straight to the mid on fielder.
Comes into the left-hander from the shorter length, Burns pushes it to the leg side.

Almost! Luck is with Burns it seems. Comes into him from outside off, on the shorter length, Rory looks to defend but the incoming ball induces an inside edge. He is lucky not to be dragging this one to his timber.
Around off, solidly blocked out.
Fuller length on the off stump, Burns brings out the drive but finds the mid off fielder.
Full and outside off, Burns looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge which flies through gully and point towards third man. A run taken.
Beaten! Good delivery. There is a slight movement and Denly has a push at this off-stump line ball, just shaped away a bit.
Landed outside off, spinning away, pushed towards point.
On a good length, Denly defneds it comfortably.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
Short in length, going away. Burns has room to cut this through square to get a single.
Full and outside off, Joe looks to defend but the ball spins in, hits the pads and lands short of Travis Head at silly point.
That turns a decent margin from the good length area from off, Denly turns this towards mid-wicket to get a single.
Fuller on the leg stump, Denly times it superbly through mid-wicket where Wade misfields and they take a couple.
FOUR! GORGEOUS! Full and outside off, Denly leans and punches it through mid off. The fielder slides to his left but the ball goes through!
On a good length outside off, Denly looks to defend but gets a bit of an inside edge onto his pads.
On a shorter length, angling into the batsman, Denly places it back to the bowler.
Around off, blocked to the off side.

A mild LBW appeal to end the session. On a good length outside off, Joe looks to defend but the ball comes in a long way and hits him on the groin. Hawk Eye shows it to be going over the stumps. TEA ON DAY 2, England trail by 114!
Starts off with a tossed up ball on off, Burns defends it solidly.
Around middle and leg, Burns waits for it and works it through mid-wicket for one. First run in the session.
Loopy ball around off, Denly pushes it back to the bowler. Three good balls to begin with by Lyon.
Slightly short this time and it is outside off, Denly has enough time to go back and push it towards cover for one.
A little too full and on the pads, it is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! A little too full and this time Lyon is hit for a boundary. It is outside off, Denly leans into the stroke and hits it through covers. An expensive start to the session by Lyon.
On the fuller side around off, Burns looks to drive but his bat turns in his hand. It goes off the inner half towards mid on for one.
Back of a length and on off, this is guided to point.
Attacks the stumps and lands it on a length. Denly keeps it out.
Cuts him into half there! This is outside off and it jags back in. Denly ends up defending outside the line and the ball sneaks between bat and pad.
Good bowling! Another one which is on a length and around off, this is kept out.
A fuller ball to end the over. Denly pushes it to mid off.
Floats it up on middle, Burns defends it.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flatter and shorter on off, it is pushed to covers.
In the air but in the gap! Slower and outside off, the batter throws his bat at it. It goes off the outer half uppishly but through covers for one.
Flatter and on off, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Floats it up on off, defended.
Back of a length and on off, Burns defends it onto the ground.
Beaten for pace! This is full and outside off, Burns is late in bringing his bat down and gets beaten.
A little too straight, this is worked behind square on the leg side for two.
Outside off and it is shorter in length. Burns plays inside the line and lets it go through to the keeper.

FOUR! Lovely shot! Not a lot wrong with the delivery. It is on a length and around off, Burns strokes it on the up past the diving mid off fielder and it races away. Burns is into the 90s. Also, England trail by below 100.
Good length and outside off, the batter shoulders arms to this one.

Well, the first ball with the new old ball, does swing. Pattinson gives the ball all the chance to swing as he bowls a full toss outside off. Denly throws his bat at it but is beaten by the away movement.
FOUR! You need not run for those! Fuller and around off, Denly strokes it right off the middle through mid off and the ball races away to the fence.
An excellent comeback! The new old ball is doing a bit. This is on off and it is on a length. The ball straightens. Denly looks to work it on the leg side but is beaten.
A little too wide outside off this time, the batter lets it be.
Closer to the off pole this time but not close enough to make the batter play.
Shorter and around middle, it jags back in. Denly looks to flick but it hits the body and rolls on the leg side.
Outside off, left alone.
On the fuller side around middle, Burns strokes it to mid on. A good shot but for no runs.
Another fuller ball on off, Burns times it to mid off.
Good length and outside off, the batter lets it be.
Another one on a length and around off, the batter pushes it to mid off.
A leave to end the over as this is outside off. A maiden.

OUT! LBW! That is plumb in front! The change of ball does the trick for Australia. Also, very good bowling by Pattinson. He set up Denly excellently. He kept taking the ball away in his last over. This time, he gets the ball to come back in. It starts from outside off, the length too is fuller. Denly looks to drive but misses as he plays outside the line. The ball hits the back pad. An appeal follows and the umpire raises the finger. Denly does have a chat with his partner but does not review. Rightly so as Hawk Eye shows three reds. A budding stand comes to an end. England are 95 away from Australia's first innings score. Another wicket quickly and Australia will be right back into the contest.
Goes back to bowling an outswinger! The length is fuller and outside off, wanting Buttler to drive. He lets it be.
On a length and around off, Buttler defends it back to the bowler who shows signs of aggression as he mimes a throw back.
A big outswinger outside off, Buttler shoulders arms to this one.
This is down the leg side, Buttler looks to flick but misses. A strange appeal from Paine but he is the only one doing so.
FOUR! Off the mark in style! A half volley outside off. Buttler does not let it go. He creams it through covers and the ball races away to the fence.
Another delivery in the 5th stump channel. Burns lets it be.

Lovely bowling! Another play and a miss! Cummins goes fuller outside off, it comes back in. Burns looks to drive but does so outside the line and gets beaten. It just looks like this guy won't get out today.
An outswinger this time outside off, Burns lets it be.
Beats the outside edge this time! This has happened too many times. It is fuller around off and it shapes away. Burns plays inside the line this time and gets beaten.
A little more wider outside off, Burns need not play at those.
Another one whizzes past the outside edge. This is around off, it pitches and goes away. Burns looks to defend but gets beaten.
Around off, this one comes back in a little. Buttler looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards mid on for a quick run.
Outside off, the batter lets it be.
Another length ball outside off, Burns makes another leave.
Burns looks really nervous at the moment. James bowls this full and outside off, Burns looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads. He is slightly late in the shot.
Another one outside off, Burns shoulders arms to this one.
Another leave which means Burns remains on 92! Shorter and outside off, this is left alone.
On the off pole, Buttler defends it out.
Around off, Buttler pushes it to covers.
Just outside off, Buttler covers his off pole and shoulders arms to this one.

OUT! Edged and taken! One brings two and that is exactly the case for Australia here. The dangerous Buttler fails to make an impact. Cummins gets his first and he is ecstatic. This is around middle and it straightens. Buttler looks to work it with the angle but the movement off the pitch does him in. It takes the leading edge and goes low to third slip. Bancroft there takes an excellent low catch diving to his right. Australia crawling their way back after the ball was changed. They hardly got any movement before and now due to the movement, they have two. England still 90 away.
This is outside off, Stokes lets it be.
Starts this on leg, it shapes away. Stokes defends it out.
A poor start by Lyon! Short and wide outside off, he gets away with it though as Burns slaps it through covers. There is protection in the deep so only a run.
This stays low! Another short one outside off, Stokes pushes it through covers for one.
Almost! This is flatter and around off, it pitches and spins away. Beats the outside edge of Burns' bat. Paine takes it and makes a muted appeal.
Slower through the air on off, defended.
Shorter in length again, Burns goes back and pushes it through covers for one.
Another short one! This time the cover fielder is in the ring so no single as Stokes pushes it straight to him.
Way too short and way too wide! Burns goes after it but misses.

FOUR! 200 up for England and Burns two runs short now of a ton. Cummins looks to go full and on the stumps, he tried to hit the pads of Burns. Rory gets his bat down in time and works it fine on the leg side for a boundary.
Onto 99 now! Fuller on off, this is pushed towards cover for one. The fielder misfields but no additional runs taken.
Good length and outside off, this is left alone.
Outside off again and this is another leave.
One more outswinger outside off, Stokes makes the third leave in a row.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Slower through the air on middle, Burns defends it out.
Big turn! This is on off, it pitches and turns away sharply. Beats the outside edge of Burns' bat who pokes at it.
On off again, it is slower through the air. Turns away one more time. Burns looks to defend but it goes off the outer half to point.
OHHH! Another play and miss! Lyon gives it a lot of loop and lands it on off, Burns plays the original trajectory but the ball spins away and beats him.
A dot to end a very good over by Lyon. Shorter and on off, this is pushed to covers. End of a brilliant over by Lyon.
On a good length around off, Stokes shuffles across and keeps it out.
Back of a length and on middle, this is pushed to mid on.
On a good length again and around off, Stokes lunges and keeps it out.
Stokes takes a few steps down the track and Siddle angles it into the batter. BS works it down to fine leg for one.
Works it with the angle towards mid-wicket but does not beat the fielder there. He remains on 99. One ball to go in this over.
Still no single! A diving stop this time. Fuller and around off, Burns strokes it towards point where the fielder stops it.
Gets Burns on strike straightaway. This is on the pads, Stokes works it towards square leg for one.
On middle, Burns works it to mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! Burns is well in! He can continue his celebration. The whole ground is on its feet to applaud the effort. His first ton and it has come at a very important time. Yes, he has had luck on his side but he still has showed great character in this knock. He gets there by working it wide of mid on. He sets off. The fielder scores a direct hit at the non-striker's end. The players appeal but Rory is already celebrating. The umpire takes it upstairs and replays show that the batter is in.
On middle, it is kept out.
Flatter and on middle, the batsman goes back and keeps it out.
BEATEN! Lovely flighted ball around off, it pitches and turns away. Stokes looks to defend but is beaten.
Shorter on off, the batter stands tall and defends it.
A little too straight, this is flicked through the leg side for one.
Outside off and on a length. It is left alone.
FOUR! Short and little room on offer, Stokes pounces on it. He plays it late and cuts it past point and into the fence. First for him.
Siddle goes fuller around off, Stokes takes a few steps down the track and pushes it to mid off.
Looks to repeat the shot he played two balls ago. This time though he can't beat point.
On the middle and leg, Burns pushes it straight to mid-wicket.
Full and down the leg side, flicked through square leg for a single.
EDGED, FOUR! On the off stump, turning away from the left-hander. Stokes throws the kitchen sink at it, the ball flies over second slip and races away to the fence.
Landed outside off, spinning away, punched towards cover.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Turns slightly from the middle stump towards off but is shorter length, the batsman shoulders arms to this one.
Drives straight to the fielder. This was wide and full.
That is loose. In the channel outside off, a touch wide, short of fuller length, Rory looks to drive hard but misses.
Around middle, worked wide of mid on for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Slightly fuller from Siddle, comes into the pads of the left-hander, Stokes times it straight to the mid-wicket fielder.
Pitches on the middle stump, Burns clips it towards the leg side and takes a single.
FOUR! CRASH! Stokes looks to be ready to play the attacking role now. Full and outside off, Stokes gets down and mows the slog sweep, all along the ground, through mid-wicket!
Lands in on the middle this time, slightly shorter in length, Stokes pushes it straight to the bowler.
Full and outside off, pushed to the off side.
Similar line from Lyon, this time the ball shapes away from the off stump, Stokes is not going to fiddle around with it.
Full on middle and leg, flicked towards mid on.
On middle and leg, helped through mid-wicket for a single.
WIDE!  That's what you get from a part-timer. Throws one way outside off and the umpire calls it wide. An extra run.
Outside off, played through point for one.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
A short ball, on middle, pulled through mid-wicket for a couple.
Another short ball, this is pulled through mid-wicket again, for another brace.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot for a couple of runs.
Down the leg side, Stokes looks to heave but misses and is hit on the thigh pad.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Around off, watchfully blocked out.
On middle and off, slightly fuller, well blocked out to the bowler.
EDGED, FOUR! Full and outside off, Ben looks to paddle but gets a top edge over short fine leg for a boundary!
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! That is really poor. Short and outside off, Burns rocks back and punches it through the covers for a boundary!
Short again, punched through point for a single.
That is bad long hop, but luckily for Head, it stays low. Stokes looking to punch this from the off stump has to crouch and the ball goes off the toe end of the bat towards cover.
Outside off, punched through the covers for a couple.
Full and outside leg, flicked straight to short leg.
Miscue but safe. Fractionally short outside off, Burns gets down on a knee and looks to pull but mistimes it over James Pattinson running back from mid on. A couple taken.
A touch short, on middle and leg, helped straight to short leg.
On leg and middle, watchfully blocked from the crease.
Full and around middle, pushed towards cover.
Full and around leg stump, blocked in an ugly manner towards mid on.
Around off, pushed towards point.
Comes down the track and blocks it out.
Around off, watchfully blocked out.
Full and around off, almost a yorker, but it is nicely jammed out.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Short and outside off, cut straight to point.
Full and outside off, Burns gets down to sweep but the ball goes off the toe end of the bat towards short leg.

Confusion, safe! Short and outside off, Burns cuts it through cover and sets off for a single. But Stokes sends him back. The striker is almost halfway down the track before he makes a U-turn. The throw is a bit high and by the time Paine can jump, collect and disturb the stumps, Burns seems to have dived back in. Aleem Dar still wants a confirmation and his colleague in the air-conditioned room gives him that with a NOT OUT signal.
Full and around leg, watchfully pushed back.
Full and around middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Oohhh... Rory looks to work it to the leg side but gets a thick leading edge which goes wide of cover. The batsmen take a single.
That shoots low, Stokes looks to play that from the crease but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Fuller length on the fifth stump line on the off side, Burns blocks it easily towards mid on.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Short on middle and off, shapes into the keeper after going past the batsman who shoulders arms to that one.

DEAD BALL. On a good length around leg, Rory shoulders arms to it. The ball goes off his back thigh and flies past the slip cordon to the third man fence. The crowd gets excited but Aleem Dar calmly signals dead ball.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
On middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Pitches it on the good length but the ball is on the leg stump, Stokes pushes it towards the leg side to take a single.

Waste of a review. Pitched miles outside leg. Rory looked to defend but missed and was hit on the pads. Pattinson appealed but the umpire was unmoved. No Australian was really interested in the review but Patto called his skipper and convinced him to take the DRS, with 2 seconds left. No use.
Short in length on the middle stump, but the ball shapes away from the left-hander towards the off side, Paine collects it behind the wicket with a dive.
Full and down the leg side, flick shot missed.
Another fifth stump line on a shorter length, Burns shoulders arms.
Another short of length ball but the line is not right again. It is on the leg stump and the batsman attempts a flick but misses.
On a good length, in the corridor of uncertainty, the batsman shoulders arms again.
This time he makes the batsman play. It was on the good length, Stokes' dab gets an inside edge and thuds to his pad.
Charges down the track to Cummins but has to adjust to the shortened length and bunts it towards mid on.
Stokes cuts this fourth stump line short delivery on the off side to run a quick couple. 50-RUN STAND IS UP!
FOUR! GLORIOUS! Overpitched outside off, Stokes comes forward and drives it down the ground. Mid off has no chance.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball. One run added to the total. 250 UP FOR ENGLAND!
On a length around middle, Stokes looks to tuck it to the leg side but gets a thick outside edge which flies through gully. A single taken.
WIDE. A bouncer on middle, Burns ducks. The umpire signals one for the over.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
Around off, blocked from the crease.

On middle and leg, Burns tucks this through mid-wicket and comes back for the second. The throw is a wild one, which comes at the bowler's end. First, umpire Wilson has to get out of the way and poor Stokes, in trying to avoid getting hit, almost falls onto the stumps.
Almost. Full and outside off, Rory looks to drive but misses.
Outside off, RB looks to drive but gets a bottom edge back to the bowler.
Short and outside off, punched towards cover.
This is outside off, punched behind point for a single. The deficit is now 29.

FOUR! Pain for Paine! Not so for Rory. It is all going his way. The pitch is now starting to show all kinds of tricks. This is short and outside off, Burns goes back to cut but the ball stays low, shoots in, takes the inside edge and goes between the keeper's legs to the fence behind!
Landed outside off, RB looks to cut but ends up slicing it towards backward point. Lands just short.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
That is a pearler. Lyon tosses this up outside leg, Burns looks to defend but the ball pitches and then whizzes past the outside edge. Superb bowling, without luck.
Brave leave. Full and outside off, Stokes shoulders arms. To his horror, the ball jags back in, but well away from the off stump.
Fractionally short, outside off, Ben pulls but finds short mid-wicket.
This one jags back in off a length, BS looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the pads.
Around off, pushed towards point.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.

FOUR! Wrong line and punished. Siddle strays on the pads, down the leg side, fractionally short of a full length, Stokes gets across and just gives it direction past Paine to the fine leg fence. There is a fielder who moves to his left but cannot get there.
Full and outside off, pushed towards point.
Full and just around middle and off, Burns lunges and keeps it out to the leg side.
Short and outside off, Rory cuts it through point. The ball does not make it to the fence and Stokes wants three but Burns is not keen on running too hard at the moment.
Around off, punched back to the bowler.
Full and around off, RB lunges to block but the ball lands on the rough and whizzes past the outside edge.
Full and around middle, spinning away, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and straight, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Landed outside off, angling away, shouldered arms to.

On a length around leg, Stokes tucks it through square leg, again he charges hard for the first, turns back quickly for the second but then sees a tired Burns just parking himself at the striker's end. Retreats, does the big Ben.
On a length around off, moving away, Burns lets it go.
Full and outside off, slightly tempting, but Rory controls himself.

Full and outside off, RB drives it through cover but Nathan Lyon dives full length to his left from point and makes a half-stop, parrying it to cover. Now, Burns wants a single but this time, Stokes wants him to take some rest.
Full and outside leg, Stokes looks to flick but the ball spins away, takes the leading edge and goes to backward point!
Fired in on middle and leg, Ben keeps it out towards short fine leg.
Faster and straighter from Gazza, Ben looks to defend but the ball scoots through, takes the inside edge and escapes to short fine leg.
Full and outside off, pushed towards mid off.
Around middle, spinning away, Ben goes back and works it wide of mid on for a single. Stokes' day is done.
Full and around leg, pushed towards mid on. STUMPS ON DAY 2, ENGLAND TRAIL BY 17!
Pattinson steams in and bowls a very full ball on off. Stokes gets on his front foot and plays a classic front foot defense to it.
Pattinson is once again on the money with a full ball on middle and off, Stokes though is concentrated and defends it.
Good ball. First ball of the day that is pitched on a good length area. It pitches on off and moves away. Stokes puts his bat to defend but misses.

WOW! What swing! This one does not go to the keeper but it goes between first slip and second slip. Good length ball outside off, the ball swings way, way too much. Smith puts his right hand out at second slip and looks to stop but fails to do so cleanly and the first run of the day comes in the shape of a bye.
Outside off on a length, Burns looks to defend but gets beaten. This one does not swing as wildly as the previous one.
Back of a length ball on off, Burns feels the ball on his willow for the first time today and defends it back towards the bowler.
Cummins starts off with a back of a length ball around off, Stokes goes back and keeps it out.
Just outside off, Stokes makes a good leave after covering his off pole.
Good fielding! Slightly fuller and on off, Stokes creams it towards cover. The fielder dives to his left and pushes it towards mid off. Saves three for his side.
On a good length and around off, this is defended nicely. No movement for Cummins as of now.
This one is angled away from the off pole, the batter need not play at those.
A dot to end as the last ball is kept out off the back foot.
Full on off, Stokes defends it towards mid on. Pattinson has a stare at Stokes but Ben is not interested.

A good looking drive but straight to the fielder. Fuller on off, Stokes plays a handsome off drive but straight towards Siddle at mid off. He misfields but that costs no run though the Barmy Army likes that.
Back of a length ball on off, Stokes plays a well-controlled pull shot towards deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Fuller again on middle, Stokes pushes it to mid on.
Good length ball just outside off, Stokes stands tall and punches it to cover.

Huge appeal but umpire Wilson is unmoved. Yorker outside off, Stokes looks to hit it but looks like he misses. There is some noise as the ball goes to Paine behind. He goes up in a confident appeal but Pattinson does not. Wilson too is unmoved. Maybe the noise was Stokes' bat hitting the ground.
Length delivery on off, Burns strokes it to point.
Full on off, Burns pushes it back towards the bowler.
Bouncer! First one of the day. It is on the body, Burns though sits under it without any trouble.
Good length ball outside off, Burns is not going to tease that and he leaves it alone.

Very good delivery this. Cummins hits the deck hard on a length. It pitches just outside off and moves away. Burns looks to defend but the ball misses the outside edge of the bat on its way to the keeper.
Back of a length ball outside off, Burns sways away from it.
FOUR! Excellent shot this! Overpitched delivery on middle and leg, Stokes picks it early and drives it through mid on to fetch the first boundary of the day.
BEATEN! Pattinson goes fuller and outside off, not very full, just behind a driving length. Stokes goes after it but does not connect.
This time he connects with the drive but can't get past covers.
This is outside off, the batter lets it be.
Good length and on off, this is blocked.
Another one on a length and around off, Stokes plays it late and to the man at gully.
A little too straight, Burns works it to mid-wicket.
Another ball which is a little too straight, Burns works it around the corner and takes one.
Back of a length around off, Stokes guides it to point.
Good length and on off, Stokes is solid in defense.

EDGY FOUR! England now trail by only 4. Stokes comes down the track and Cummins shortens the length. Stokes looks to defend but due to the angle away, it goes off the outside edge and down to the third man fence.
Back of a length on off, Stokes keeps it out.
Shorter and around off, Burns guides it to point.
Another shorter in length delivery which is guided to point.
Another length ball around off, Burns plays it late as he guides it down to third man for one.

Fifty for Ben Stokes! His good form in the ODI format has been carried forward in the longest version. Also, it has been a very fluent and a good innings to watch. He would be eyeing a big one here. He jams this very full ball on off towards mid off for a quick run. 18th Test fifty for him.
Good length and on off, this is guided to point.
Slightly shorter around off, Burns guides it to the man at point.

OUT! Caught behind! Australia finally, finally manage to breakthrough this 88-run stand. Stokes departs immediately after getting to his half ton. An early wicket for the visitors, just what they wanted. Cummins is the man who gets him. His second. This is slightly short and just outside off. Stokes plays the wrong shot as he looks to cut. The ball is too close to play that shot. The outside edge is taken and Paine does not make a mistake behind. Half the side back in the hut for England and they are still two runs away from Australia's score.
Good length and on off, this is defended.
Back of a length and on off, Bairstow defends it onto the ground.
Another length ball on off, JB keeps it out.
This is angled into the batter, Bairstow looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Jonny Bairstow is off the mark! This is around off, JB pushes it towards point and takes off. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
An appeal but that is off the arm! This is shorter and on the body, Bairstow looks to evade it but the ball hits the arm and lobs to the keeper.
FOUR! ENGLAND ARE INTO THE LEAD! That has gone to the fence like a tracer bullet. A little too straight by Pattinson. Bairstow flicks it through square leg and the ball races away to the fence.
Corrects his line and lands it on off, JB defends it out.
Edge, short! This is around off and on a length. Bairstow looks to defend but does so inside the line. It goes off the outside edge but well short of second slip.
Around off and on a length, Bairstow flicks it uppishly but once again well short of the fielder at mid-wicket.
Too straight on middle, Bairstow works it through square leg for one. The fielder was in the deep this time so just a single.
Just outside off, Jonny shoulders arms to this one. The ball does not carry to the keeper.
Outside off, Bairstow goes hard at it but mistimes it to mid off.
This is angled into the batter, Jonny works it to mid-wicket.
Another ball on a length and around off, JB blocks it out.
Shorter and outside off, Bairstow looks to force it through the off side but misses.
Well bowled again! Goes wide of the crease and angles it on off, it straightens a touch. Bairstow looks to push at it again but is beaten again.
Floats it up on middle, Burns defends it nicely.
Sharp turn! We saw a lot of that yesterday. We saw a lot of beating of the outside edge too. This is flatter and on off, it pitches and spins away sharply. Burns looks to defend but gets beaten.
A little fuller on off, Burns strokes it to covers.
Too short outside off, Burns slaps it through covers for one.
Floats it up on off, JB goes back and keeps it out.
Loopy ball around off, Bairstow works it with the turn to mid-wicket.
Fullish and on off, Burns pushes it to mid off.
Another one whizzes past the outside edge! Siddle goes fuller and around off, it is angling away. Burns looks to drive but misses.
Back of a length on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! First boundary of the day for Burns. Full again and way too outside off, Burns reaches out for it and strokes it through cover-point.
Another fuller ball around off, RB strokes it to mid off.
Another fuller ball on off, Burns plays it to short cover.
Well fielded! This is on off, Bairstow goes back and works it with the turn towards short leg who dives to his right and stops it.
A muted appeal! This pitches outside off and then turns back in. Bairstow goes back and looks to flick but misses to get hit above the pads.
Tossed up outside off, JB covers his off pole and shoulders arms to this one.
Shorter and quicker outside off, Bairstow initially looks to cut but then bails out.
On the stumps, Bairstow works it to mid-wicket.
A dot to end a good over by Lyon! On off, the batter goes back and keeps it out.
Around off and angling away, Burns plays it late down to third man for one. The lead is now into double figures.
Easy pickings this! This is on middle, it is flicked down towards fine leg for two.
Fuller and on off, Bairstow strokes it to mid off.
Slashes and misses! Shorter in length and outside off, JB looks to slap it but misses.
Attacks the off pole, Bairstow defends it out.
Another one on off, Bairstow guides it to point.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Burns' long, wonderful innings comes to an end!  It has taken a peach an absolute peach to get rid of the man. Lyon floats it on off, it pitches and spins away quickly. Burns looks to defend but ends up getting a faint outside edge towards Paine. He takes the catch and goes up in celebration. Burns walks off to a huge standing ovation, he shows his bat to the crowd to soak in all the applause. But hold on a minute, the umpires check for the no ball and.... Lyon is just in by a whisker. Burns who was hoping to come back has to continue his walk.

FOUR BYES! On the pads, Moeen looks to flick but the ball deflects off the pads and goes fine down the leg side. Siddle runs to his right and looks to pull it back before the ropes but unfortunately ends up slipping in the process.
Floated on the pads, Moeen defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle, Moeen keeps it out.
On the stumps, Moeen keeps it out.

OUT! Bowled! Moeen has been cleaned up and not in a smart-looking manner. His poor run of form with the bat continues. Lyon flights one on middle and off, Moeen expects it to turn away and leaves it alone. The ball takes the off pole on its way. Lyon has a laugh. Don't know what Moeen was thinking when he decided to leave the ball. Probably the first ball Lyon bowled to Root, yesterday, was in his mind. He might have felt this would also turn a long way but it does not. Now though he will be reminded of this wicket by everyone. End of a brilliant over from Lyon! Two wickets in it and Australia are now into the fast bowlers.
On a good length and around off, this is defended.
Back of a length again on off, Bairstow stands tall and defends it onto the ground.
Slightly fuller and around off, it comes back in. JB strokes it back towards the bowler who makes a half-stop but no runs taken.
On middle, Jonny once again keeps it out.

OUT! Taken at slip! Another one bites the dust! Australia right back in the contest. England have completely lost their way here. From 282 for 4, England have slipped to 300 for 8. Siddle bowls this slightly short and outside off. Bairstow makes the same mistake Stokes did. He goes after it but there was not enough width on offer. It goes off the outside edge and quickly towards Warner at first slip. He takes a sharp catch. England's lead only reads 16. They have two wickets left.
On middle, Broad blocks it out. End of a successful over from Siddle.
Flighted outside off, Woakes defends it off the inner half of his bat.
Off spinner on middle, Woakes gets on his back foot and punches it to cover.
Flighted outside off, Woakes looks to defend but the ball hits him on the back pad.
Tossed up on off, Woakes comes down the track and strokes it to long on for one.
Very full on middle and leg, Broad defends it off the inner half of his bat to the side of the pitch on the leg side.
Tossed up on middle, Broad this time defends it off the front foot off right off the meat of his bat.
Good length and on off, Woakes defends it late and it goes towards gully.
This is shorter and on middle, Woakes pushes it to mid on.
That was played awkwardly! Shorter and on middle, Woakes plays the no-watch-pull shot. He connects well though and it goes through square leg for one.
Another single as this is worked towards fine leg for one. Broad is off the mark.
Shorter and around off, Woakes pushes it to mid off.
Cummins rolls his fingers on this one outside off. Woakes lets it be.

Well played and well fielded! Broad brings the sweep shot out. He hits it through backward square leg. Head runs to his left in the deep, dives and pushes it back towards Siddle who runs after the ball from short fine leg. The teamwork saves one.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Down the leg side, Woakes lets it be.
Another one on the pads, Woakes lets it be and it hits the pads.

Uppish but wide! Flatter and on off, Woakes goes back to defend. The ball spins back in sharply. It takes the inside edge which deflects onto the pads but goes wide of the fielder at short leg for one.
On middle, Broad keeps it out.
Good length ball on middle, Woakes flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a single.
A huge cheer from the crowd as Broad strokes this length ball outside off towards point for a couple.
Back of a length ball close to the body, Broad does well to defend it wide of short leg.
Fuller on off, Broad defends it with soft hands. It goes towards gully all along the ground off the outer half of his bat.
Come around the wicket and bowls it on top of middle, Broad defends it towards cover and takes a single. Every run being cheered from the crowd here.
Over the wicket to the right hander. It is on a length on off, Woakes defends it to get through the over unharmed.
Nicely swept but straight to the man. Flighted outside off, Broad sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.

Huge appeal but nothing. Tossed up outside off, it spins in. Woakes looks to defend but the ball lobs up of his pad towards first slip. The Aussies appeal but nothing from the umpire. They do not take their last remaining review.

Excellent fielding! Flighted on off, Woakes looks to turn it away to the left of Bancroft at short leg. Cameron though stretches out and shows good reflection as he stops the ball. He quickly releases the ball to the keeper but Woakes is quick to get in.
Floated on off, Woakes strokes it through covers for one.
Slower through the air on off, Broad defends it off the front foot.
Floated on the stumps, Broad keeps it out.
Fuller ball on off, Woakes defends it off the front foot.
Pacy ball on off and middle, Woakes blocks it off his front foot.
Outside off, tempting Woakes to drive but Chris does not fall into the trap and leaves it alone.
Closer to the off pole, Woakes defends it to cover and shouts a loud no to his partner.
Good length ball on off, Woakes defends it with straight bat towards mid on.
Very good shot but also good fielding. Away swinging ball full on off,  Woakes drives it hard but to the right of Bancroft at covers.
Flighted outside off, Broad sweeps it to square leg for a single.
Woakes comes down the track and whips it towards mid-wicket for another single.
Nicely bowled and nicely played. Tossed up on off, Broad blocks it out.
'Well done Garry boy!' is the shout from the skipper as he flights it on off. Broad blocks it.
Tossed up on middle, Broad paddles it towards short fine leg for a single.
FOUR BYES! BEATS EVERYONE! Flighted on leg, Woakes looks to defend but the ball spins in and goes between the bat and pad. It misses the stumps and the keeper as it goes to the fence.
Back of a length ball on off, Broad punches it to cover.
Nicely played. It is once again short, Broad squeezes it through point and gets a single.
Full outside off, Woakes pushes it to mid off.
On the pads, Woakes turns it to the on side for a single. The partnership now moves to 22.
Back of a length ball on off, Broad defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery on off, Broad defends it off the front foot and get closer to Lunch.

SIX! That was six the moment it left the bat. Floated on off, Woakes gets down on one knee and smokes it over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie. Smart batting this as he saw mid-wicket come in from the deep.
Tossed up on off, Woakes comes down the track and strokes it to mid off.
Outside off and after two aggressive looking strokes he calmly leaves this one.
Flighted on off, CW comes down the track and blocks it.
Back foot defense this time. Shorter on off, Woakes defends it off the back foot.
Flighted outside off, Woakes shoulders arms to it. That is the end of the first session on Day 3.
Attacks the stumps from around the wicket, Broad keeps it out.
Full and outside off, Broad makes a leave.
First run of this session! On the pads, SB works it towards fine leg and gets to the other end.
Edgy run! This is a top nut! Squares Chris Woakes up. It pitches on middle and straightens. Woakes looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge down to third man for one.
Fuller in length and outside off, the batter lets it be.
Closer to the off pole but not close enough to make the batter play.
This is floated up on off, Woakes comes down the track and strokes it back to the bowler.
Flatter and on the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Well bowled! Gives it a little more air and lands it around off, draws Broad into a drive. The ball though turns away and beats the outside edge.

FOUR! Lead over 50 now! Another sweep shot by Broad. He is playing that shot really well. He drags this from outside off and gets it through mid-wicket. Away from the fielder in the deep and a boundary.
A single now! The arm ball around middle, Broad looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards short fine leg for one.
Misread the length there Woakes! Flatter and fuller outside off, Woakes goes back and looks to cut but misses. Too full to play that shot.
A yorker outside off, Broad jams it out.
BEATEN! Extra pace there! Pattinson bends his back on this one and bangs it short around off. Broad looks to force it through the off side but misses.
Good shot but for no runs! Shorter and around off, Broad pushes it to point.
This stays low! Well played in the end by Broad. This is on off, Broad gets his bat down in time and guides it down to third man for one.
On a good length around off, Woakes defends it out.
A little too straight, Woakes works it through mid-wicket and takes two. This stand continues to frustrate Australia.
Flatter and quicker on middle, Broad pushes it to covers.
Floats it up on middle, Broad keeps it out.
Fires this one outside off, Broad pushes it through the off side for one.
Shorter and around off, Woakes goes back and pushes it to covers.
This pitches outside off and turns back in. Woakes goes back and works it with the turn through square leg for one.
This is a flighted ball on middle, it is defended.
On middle, Woakes defends it out.
Shortish in length and outside off, Woakes slaps it but finds point.
A bumper but it does not rise a lot. Woakes pulls it down to fine leg and takes one.
From around the wicket, this is angled into the off pole. Broad keeps it out.
Shorter and around off, Broad pushes it through covers for one.
This is on middle, it is worked through square leg for one.
Flatter and on middle, Woakes goes back and keeps it out.
Floats it up on off, Woakes eases it down to long on with the turn for one.
Almost got bowled around his legs! Lyon pitches this outside leg and gets it to straighten. Broad looks to sweep but misses. It misses the leg pole by a little.
This time connects with the sweep shot but finds short fine leg.
On off, Broad lunges and keeps it out.
Another solid defensive stroke to this flighted ball on middle.
A slower one on middle, Woakes picks it and works it through square leg for one.
Shorter and on off, it comes slow off the surface. Broad guides it down to third man for one.
BEATEN! Not the right length to drive. Behind a driving length outside off, Woakes looks to push at it but misses.
Attacks the off pole, this time Woakes defends it out.
Well played! This is around off and it straightens. Woakes looks to defend it with soft hands. It goes off the outside edge towards second slip where Smith fumbles and the batters take one.
A yorker on middle, SB jams it out.
Flatter and on off, Woakes pushes it back to the bowler. It has been signaled as a no ball! Australia had two fielders behind square.
On off again, Woakes goes back and defends it out easily.
Uses his feet this time and the batter strokes it down to long on for one. The 50-run stand is also up, a vital, vital one for England. Also, this is surely frustrating Australia. 350 up for England.
On middle, Broad defends it.
Now once again plays the shot he has played so well till now, the sweep, he drags it from outside off through mid-wicket for one.
Good running! This is flatter and on off, Woakes drops it towards the off side and takes one. Every run is being cheered now.
A loopy ball on middle, Broad defends it onto the ground.
Cummins steams in and bowls it full on middle and leg, Woakes flicks it to the right of deep mid-wicket and gets a single.
Comes around the wicket and bowls a good length ball on top of off, Broad plays it wide of gully towards backward point for a single.
No bouncers yet. This is full on off, Woakes strokes it back to the bowler.
Very full on middle and off. Almost a yorker. Woakes digs it to the right of the bowler.
Good length ball on off, Woakes defends it with absolute calmness.
Just close to off pole, Woakes defends it towards cover-point and gets through the over.
Gives it air and lands it outside off, Broad pushes it towards cover and takes one.
A full toss on middle, Woakes pushes it to mid on.
On middle, this is defended onto the ground.
Fuller and on middle, Woakes works it to mid-wicket.
The googly on middle, Woakes nudges it around the corner and takes one.
The googly on off, it pitches and turns away. Broad looks to defend but gets beaten.
Good length ball outside off, Woakes strokes it towards third man and gets to the other end. The Barmy Army is cheering every run.

Finally a short ball that rises. First one from Cummins in this spell. It is on the body, Broad hops up and looks to keep it down. The ball hits his inside edge onto the body but more importantly does not lob anywhere else.
Yorker on off, Broad digs it out to point.
On top of off, Broad plays it to point.
Nicely played. Another short ball around the hips of Broad. He hops and keeps it down with a tuck.
On top of middle and off, Broad blocks it to get through the over.
A full toss on middle, Woakes works it through mid-wicket. There is protection in the deep so just a run.
Floats it up on off, Broad defends it out.

FOUR! Fortunate runs! A little bottom edge. Nothing the keeper could do there. This is floated outside off, Broad looks to sweep but the ball hits the bottom part of the bat and goes between the legs of the keeper for a boundary in the fine leg region.
This time he connects with the sweep shot nicely and it goes through square leg for one.
Loopy ball on off, Woakes strokes it down to long off for a single.
Flighted delivery around off, Broad lunges and keeps it out.
Back of a length on off, this is defended.
Around off, Woakes defends it out.
Another one on the stumps, Woakes is solid in defense.
On the fuller side on off, Woakes pushes it to mid off.
Shorter and on off, Woakes guides it down to third man and a single is taken.
A sharp bumper to end! Broad does well to evade it.
Outside off, it has been left alone.
Outside off and shorter in length. Woakes looks to cut but due to the ball turning back in, he ends up chopping it to the off side.
Flatter and on off, Woakes defends it out.
Comes down the track but gets too close to the pitch of the ball. It is jammed back to the bowler.
Flatter and on off, Woakes once again pushes it back to the bowler.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Cummins bowls it on a good length on leg, Broad tucks it to the leg side.
Short of a length delivery outside leg, Broad looks to go after it but misses it.
Bowls a sharp bouncer, Broad does well to duck under it.
Bowls a slower bouncer, Broad ducks underneath it.
On a good length on middle, Broad blocks it off the back foot.

OUT! In the air... taken! The frustrating stand, very frustrating stand actually comes to an end. The ploy to keep bowling short to Broad works. This however, isn't exactly short. It bounces around the stomach of Broad. He whips it, does not keep it down and Pattinson at fine leg takes a good catch. A good little innings by Broad comes to an end. He has surely done his job with the bat here. England lead by 81. One wicket in hand. Can they get to 100?
On middle, this is kept out.
Flatter and on off, Anderson keeps it out.
Another one on the stumps, Anderson is successful in defending it.
Looks to score, he brings out the reverse sweep but finds the man at point.
Slower through the air on off, Anderson prods forward and keeps it out.
On the stumps again, Anderson once again defends it out. He survives the whole over.
On a good length and around off, Woakes keeps it out.
Good length delivery outside off, Woakes defends it out.
On a good length on middle, Woakes defends it off the back foot.
Full and outside off, Woakes drives it through covers. He denies the single.
Full on off, Woakes drives it to mid off.
Bowls it very wide outside off, Woakes looks to slash it but misses it.
An appeal but not given! This is fired on the pads, Anderson looks to sweep but misses to get hit on the pads. That is going down leg.
On middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.
On the off pole, Anderson manages to defend it out.
A single as Anderson connects with the sweep. There is a man in the deep square leg region.
Woakes comes down the track but Lyon shortens his length. Woakes keeps it out.
Takes the single off the last ball as he paddles it towards short fine leg. Good running.
Full and outside off, Woakes drives it hard through covers. Bancroft chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen don't take the single.
Good length delivery on off, Woakes defends it out.
EDGY FOUR! England won't mind how they come as long as they come. Fuller and outside off, Woakes throws his bat at it. It flies off the outside edge and down to the third man fence.
Back of a length and on off, Woakes keeps it out.
A yorker on off, this is jammed out to point.
A swing and a miss! Short and outside off, Woakes looks to go over mid-wicket but misses. A dot to end which means Anderson will be on strike.
Well bowled! Goes around the wicket and angles it into the off pole, gets the ball to straighten after pitching. Anderson looks to defend but is beaten.

Off the edge but does not carry! Fuller around off, Anderson, who is ready for the short one, stays rooted to his crease and looks to push at it. It goes off the outside edge towards second slip where the fielder stops it well.
Very full again on middle, Anderson is ready for it and he jams it out.

A couple! Should have been three though. This is on off and it is on a length. Anderson pushes it through cover-point. Head gives it a chase and right at the end, pushes it back in with a dive. The fielder from third man does the mopping up job.
Short but it just does not bounce a lot. Anderson easily works it to fine leg.
And he negotiates the last ball nicely! On off, this is kept out.
Flatter and on middle, Woakes works it to mid-wicket.
Nicely played! Brings the paddle sweep out towards fine leg but only for one. Woakes maybe trusts Anderson to play Lyon out.
Does play this ball nicely! This is on the pads, Anderson works it to short fine leg.
Turn and bounce! The important thing for England is, Anderson survives. This is a loopy ball outside off, Anderson looks to drive but gets beaten by the away turn.

OUT! In the air... taken! Lyon ends things. Anderson's patience runs out. He looks to go over the mid-wicket region but only manages a top edge due to the extra bounce Lyon extracts. It goes high up in the air and Cummins at mid-wicket takes a dolly. Also, TEA HAS BEEN TAKEN! ENGLAND ALL OUT FOR 374!
Good length and on off, Bancroft keeps it out.
A huge appeal by the bowler but it is too high! This is around off and it comes back in. The length is shorter. Bancroft looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads.

Beauty! Broad has started brilliantly. Got the last ball to come in and takes this one away. It lands on off and on a length. Straightens. Bancroft looks to defend but is beaten. The ball flicks the outside part of the bat and goes to the keeper.
Australia are underway! A good length ball on off, CB drops it towards cover and takes off. There is a shy at the striker's end but misses.
Broad straightaway goes around the wicket and angles it into the batter. Warner works it to mid-wicket.
A dot to end a very good first over by Broad. This is again angled into the batter. Warner hops and keeps it out.
Good length and on middle, Bancroft defends it to mid on.
Way too wide outside off, a little shape away for Woakes. Bancroft need not play at those.

This is lovely, lovely bowling! He too like Broad, got the last one to move away and gets this one back in from outside off. Not enough though to make the batter play. However, that went pretty close past the off pole.
Around off, this is defended.
Outside off, CB shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Easy-peasy! First boundary of this innings. It is on the pads, Bancroft loves it there. He flicks it through square leg and the ball races away to the fence.
Good length ball on off, Warner looks to defend but the inward movement sees the ball hit Warner's inner half of his bat onto his pad.
FOUR! Warner is up and running! Broad overpitches it around off, Warner picks the length early and drives it right off the sweet spot of his bat through mid off for a boundary.

EDGED AND FOUR! A very good boundary is followed by a streaky boundary. Broad pulls his length back and bowls it in the good length area. It swings away after pitching. Warner looks to defend it but ends up getting a thick outside edge. There is no gully or third man so the ball goes through that region and races away to the fence.
Outside off on a fourth stump line, Warner shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball closer to the off pole but not close enough to make Warner play.

OUT! Caught! Very good review from England and Warner's return to Test cricket is an unsuccessful one. He becomes Broad's 450th victim in Test cricket. Broad after conceding two boundaries in the over bowls an absolute jaffa! Back of a length ball around off. It is a line which questions the batsman. Warner is in double mind to play or leave that. He initially looks to play but then decides to leave. He is late in his decision as when he looks to leave the ball kisses his outside edge and goes to the right of the keeper. Bairstow takes the catch and goes up in celebration. The umpire though is unmoved and Root takes the review. Replays roll in and it shows there is a good amount of edge on it. The English crowd are up in joy. Warner walks back disappointed. Early setback for Australia. Usman Khawaja replaces him out in the middle.
On a good length and outside off, Bancroft shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery outside off, Bancroft lets it go.
Third consecutive leave from Cameron Bancroft. Outside off, Bancroft leaves it alone.
Length delivery on off, Bancroft plays it to point.
On a good length on middle, Bancroft flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on off, Bancroft keeps it out.
Pitches on the fifth stump line and comes in. Khawaja is aware of his off stump and leaves it alone.
This one moves away. It is outside off, Khawaja has no business with it.
Outside off, once again Khawaja lets it carry to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Khawaja shoulders arms to it.
Fuller on the off pole, Khawaja pushes it to cover.
Khawaja is off the mark! Full ball on the pads, Khawaja flicks it towards fine leg and gets a single.
Khawaja flicks it away with a wristy shot. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Length delivery on off, Bancroft plays it to covers.
On a good length and outside off, Bancroft looks to defend but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Good length delivery on off, Bancroft blocks it off the front foot.
On a length on off, Bancroft plays it to point.
On a good length and outside off, Bancroft lets it go.
Full ball on the pads, Khawaja glances it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Khawaja leaves it alone.
Full on off, Khawaja defends it with soft hands wide of cover and gets a single.
Outside off and swinging away, Bancroft shoulders arms to it.
Edged but safe! Length delivery on off, it swings away after pitching. Bancroft looks to defend with soft hands but ends up getting a thick outside edge. Luckily it falls well short of gully.
On the body, Bancroft glances it to fine leg and keeps the strike with an easy single.
Starts with an off spinner around off, Bancroft defends it off the back foot.

Beauty! This has spun a lot. Flighted outside off, Bancroft looks to defend but the ball goes past the bat and pad. The keeper too cannot gather it cleanly and the ball goes towards the fine leg region for a bye.
FOUR! Not off the middle but Khawaja will take it.  Floated on off, Khawaja looks to defend but the ball goes off the outer half of his bat through the third man region for a boundary.
Tossed up on the stumps, Khawaja defends it off the front foot.
Flighted outside off, Khawaja sweeps it towards mid-wicket for a couple.
Shorter on middle and leg, Khawaja glances it towards mid-wicket for a couple.
Good length ball outside off, Bancroft leaves it alone.
Outside off once again, Bancroft leaves it alone.
Good ball. Broad steams in a good length ball around off, Bancroft looks to defend but the ball zips away after pitching beating Bancroft's outside edge on its way to the keeper.
Length delivery on off, Bancroft shuffles to his off pole and pushes it towards cover for a single.
Length ball outside off, Usman lets it carry to the keeper.
Fuller on middle, Khawaja pushes it to mid on.

OUT! Caught! The idea to bring the spinner in early has worked. Just like Warner, Bancroft's return is not that successful either. Floated off spinner pitching on off, it turns in nicely. Bancroft looks to defend but ends up getting an inside edge onto the pads. The ball deflects off the pads and goes to the right of short leg. Buttler there shows good reflexes and takes a very sharp catch.
Floated on off and middle, Smith defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle, Smith flicks it to mid-wicket.
Smith is off the mark. Flighted on middle and off, Smith shuffles across and glances it towards mid-wicket for one.

DROPPED! A very difficult chance but Buttler should have taken it.  Flighted delivery outside off, Khawaja looks to push it but gets a thick outside edge which goes low towards second slip. Buttler gets his fingers to it but cannot hold onto it. It goes behind him and they take a single.
FOUR! Smith continues his fine form from  the first innings. Floated on the pads, Smith flicks it through square leg to get his first boundary of the innings.
FOUR! Beautiful! Overpitched on middle and leg, Khawaja picks it early and glances it through mid-wicket for a glorious boundary.
FOUR! Poor from Broad. He bowls it on the hips of Khawaja, he just nudges it fine down the leg side to get the second boundary in the over.
Outside off, Khawaja has nothing to do with it.
On the pads, Khawaja tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Smith runs it down to third man, wide of the fielder and gets a couple.
Outside off, Smith strokes it towards point and gets a brace to end the over. Expensive over from Broad. 13 runs off it.
Shorter on off, Khawaja tucks it to mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Flighted on off, Khawaja blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up on the stumps, Usman defends it off the front foot.

BEATEN! Sharp turn on this one., It pitches around off and spins away. Khawaja looks to defend but gets beaten by the turn. That was not far away from the outside edge. Bairstow fails to collect it behind the stumps.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Moeen sprays this on the pads, Khawaja flicks it fine down the leg side and fetches himself another boundary.
Short on off, Khawaja punches it to cover.
Bowls a fuller ball outside off, it comes in after pitching. Smith looks to defend but the ball hits his thigh pad. There is a stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Length delivery on off, Steve defends it off the middle this time to cover.
On top of middle and off, Smith shuffles across and glances it towards square leg for a couple.
Length ball outside off, Smith looks to defend but once again misses and gets hit high on the thigh pad.
EDGED BUT SHORT! Good length ball outside off, it comes in. Smith looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. Luckily he played it with soft hands which meant it fell well short of Bairstow.
Fuller on off, Smith pushes it towards cover for a single.
Flighted around off, Smith comes down the track and whips it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted on off, Khawaja drives it straight to cover.
Tossed up around off, Usman strokes it to the left of cover and gets to the other end.
Flighted on off, Smith milks it down to long on for one.
Shorter on off, Khawaja defends it by getting right behind that on his back foot.
Very full, almost a yorker on off. Khawaja does well to get his bat down in time.
Fuller on off, Smith defends it with a straight bat.
Good length ball on off, Smith shuffles like his usual self and flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball pitching on off, it goes away with the angle. Khawaja leaves  it alone.
Fuller on off, Khawaja defends it back towards Woakes.
Ouch! Back of a length ball on off, Khawaja looks to defend but the ball hits him very high on his bat. Jarring the bottom hand.
Fuller on middle, Khawaja flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a couple as the fielder mops it up. Usman is looking good out in the middle but he needs to continue this.
Tossed up on off, Smith glances it towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Comes around the wicket and flights it on off. Khawaja milks it down to long off for one.
Shorter around off, Smith gets on his back foot and defends it.
Tossed up on off, Smith looks to flick it towards mid-wicket but gets a leading edge which goes all along the ground back to the bowler.
Off spinner pitching on off. It spins in and  Smith turns it behind square on the leg side with the spin for a single.
Floated on off, UK pushes it to cover to get through the over.

Could have been disastrous! Back of a length ball around off, Smith shuffles in and defends it towards cover-point. He comes ahead for a single but Khawaja sends him back. Good and early call as there was never a run there. Run out is the last thing the Aussies need at the moment.
On the pads, Smith nudges it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Beautiful! Full outside off, Khawaja gets on his front foot and drives it excellently through covers. The fielders from point and cover give it a chase but cannot stop it.
Follows it up with a good, solid front foot defense.
Outside off, Khawaja leaves it alone without any fuss.
FOUR! This is even better than the previous boundary. Woakes overpitches it on middle and leg, Khawaja plays a handsome on drive through mid on for a boundary.
Starts with a flighted delivery on the pads, Smith glances it towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Floated outside off, Khawaja leaves it alone.
Once again away from the off pole, Usman has nothing to do with it.
Tossed up on off, Khawaja defends it off the front foot.
Flights one on off, Khawaja plays a textbook front foot defense to it.
Slower on off, Khawaja strokes it towards extra cover and keeps the strike with a single.
Starts with a good length ball around off. It does not come very quickly. Khawaja defends it to mid off.

OUT! Caught! This is a peach of a delivery from Stokes! He bowls a scrambled seam delivery on off, it nips back in cutting Khawaja in half. He looks to defend but the ball kisses his inside edge and carries to the right of the keeper. Bairstow moves to that side and takes a good catch. The English players go up in a very confident appeal and the umpire agrees. Once again the bowling change has worked for the hosts. Khawaja cannot convert his good start here and the 48-run stand is broken. Australia still trail by 15 runs.
Another gem! Good length ball on middle and off, it comes in and cuts Head in half on its way to the keeper.
Length delivery outside off, Travis leaves it alone.
Bouncer! It is a well directed one but Travis sits under it.
Outside off and Head leaves it alone. Brilliant start for Stokes. Wicket maiden for him to begin.
Floated on off, Smith turns it behind square on the leg side and gets a single.
Bowls it very full to Travis first up. Head defends it with a straight bat.
Floated outside off, Head shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR RUNNING RUNS! Schoolboy stuff from England. Floated delivery on  middle and leg, Head flicks it through mid-wicket and they come back for the third. Roy has a shy at the keeper's end. The ball bounces just in front of Bairstow and deflects behind of his pads towards the third man region allowing them to take one more.
Tossed up on off, Head defends it off the front foot to see off Moeen Ali's over.
Length delivery on the pads, Smith glances it towards mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Smith turns it behind square on the leg side and gets a single.
Length ball on off, Head looks to defend but it comes off the bottom half of his bat.
On the fourth stump line, Head leaves it alone.
On the pads, Head glances it towards mid-wicket and gets a brace as the fielder cleans it up.
Fuller outside off, TH shoulders arms to it.
Flighted on off, Smith defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Smith drives it through covers. The ball does not have the legs to reach the fence as the fielder cleans it up. The batsmen come back for the third.
Floated on off, Head strokes it wide of cover for one.
Flights it on off, Smith calmly defends it.
Tossed up outside off, Smith reaches out and drives it to mid off.
Australia level the scores now. Smith flicks it towards mid-wicket and gets a single which nullifies Australia's deficit.
Into the lead now! Good length ball on off, Smith glances it towards mid-wicket for a single.
On the fourth stump line, Head leaves it alone.
Full on off, Head tucks it against the angle towards mid-wicket and gets a single.
On off, Smith turns it wide of fine leg and gets a couple as Moeen Ali cleans it up.
Length delivery outside off, Smith shuffles across and leaves it alone. The ball kisses his pad and goes to the keeper.
On off pole, Smith defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted on off, Head strokes it wide of mid off.
Floated on off, Head defends it with soft hands towards cover and gets a single.
On the pads, Smith waits and turns it towards fine leg and gets a couple.

Huge appeal but the impact looked to be outside off. Flighted delivery outside off, it spins in and keeps low. Smith looks to defend but misses. The ball hits his back pad and Bairstow goes up in appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Floated on off, Smith defends it by bending his back.
On the pads, Smith flicks it away to the on side and keeps the strike.

Direct hit and Head was gone for all money! Good length ball on off, Smith shuffles across and tucks it towards mid-wicket. Burns comes running in from square leg and gets to the ball quickly. He has one stump to aim at the keeper's end but misses.
Length ball outside off, Head goes for the punch but ends up chopping it back towards the keeper.
Length ball on the pads, Head glances it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Head glances it but cannot get past mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.
On the hips, Head tucks it fine down the leg side and gets a couple. It also brings up the 100 for Australia.
FOUR! Gorgeous! Moeen tosses it up on off, Smith gets on his front foot and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Shorter on middle, Smith punches it wide of mid on and gets a single.
Good running. Floated on off, Head defends it with soft hands towards cover and calls for a quick single. He gets to the other end with ease.
This keeps low! Floated on middle, Smith does well to negate the low bounce and turn it to mid-wicket.
Flighted on off, Steve whips it to mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Very full on middle and leg, Head pushes it to mid on.
Stokes misses his line and bowls it down the leg side. Steve leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Smith leaves it alone in his trademark fashion.
On top of off, Smith flicks it to square leg and shouts wait on to his partner.
Fuller on off, Smith pushes it to mid off.

Huge appeal for lbw but nothing from the umpire. Good length ball around off, Smith looks to defend but misses. The ball hits him below his box. The  English players put in a huge appeal but nothing from the umpire. Stokes thinks it is dipping but Root does not feel it is dipping enough to overturn the decision.
NO BALL! Good length ball outside off, Smith leaves it alone.
Defended off the back foot by Smith.
Pitches it on the rough outside off, Head leaves it alone.
Shorter on off, Head punches it to cover.
Floated on the stumps, Head defends it off the front foot.
On the pads, Head flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Head pushes it towards cover for a single.
On the pads, Smith turns it to the on side and gets a single.
On a good length on off, Smith plays it to point.

NASTY! Stokes bends his back and bowls a vicious short ball. Smith looks to pull but the ball goes through and hits him flush on the grill. The England players gather around Smith. He removes his helmet but will have a mandatory check here as per the protocol. Steve nods though indicating everything is all right.
Back of a length ball on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.
This time Smith pulls the short ball in a controlled manner towards mid-wicket.
On the pads, Smith flicks it but straight to square leg.
Fuller on off, Smith defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up wide outside off, Head leaves it alone.
Flighted delivery outside off, Head lets it go.
FOUR! In the air but safe. Shorter ball outside off, Head looks to cut but ends up slicing it wide. Luckily the ball goes wide and away of the man at first slip to the third man fence.
FOUR! Consecutive boundaries for Travis Head. Short and outside off, Head cuts it hard through point for a boundary.
Short again, Head cuts it to point.
Flighted delivery on off, Head defends it out.
FOUR! Pulled and pulled away hard! Short ball on off, Smith picks it early and pulls it in a controlled manner through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Now drives but straight to the man at point.
Back of a length ball on off, SS pulls it all along the ground towards mid-wicket for a single.
On top of off, Head defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Head has no business with this one and leaves it alone.
This keeps low but luckily, there is no casualty. Good length ball outside off, the ball keeps low and comes in. Luckily it does not nip in enough to hit Head's pad or the stumps.
