Another tossed up ball around off, it pitches and turns away. Stokes defends inside the line, the ball kisses the outside edge and goes into the mitts of Paine. Wickets tumbling at the moment. This can end before the Drinks Break.
FOUR! A lovely way to get off the mark! This is very full outside off, Woakes strokes it through covers and the ball races away to the fence.
Uppish but wide! Loopy ball on middle, Woakes whips it uppishly but wide of mid-wicket. Mid on does well to dive to his right and save three. Also, due to that single, Moeen Ali is on strike to Lyon.
On middle, Moeen Ali blocks it out.
Just outside off, unlike the first innings, this time, Moeen keeps his eyes on the ball and lets it be.
Another floated delivery outside off, this one pitches and turns away. Also, stays low. Moeen makes a leave.
FOUR! Something for the English fans to cheer about! Full outside off, Woakes drives it uppishly but in the gap through point for a boundary.
FOUR LEG BYES! Cummins bowls this fast but on the pads, Woakes looks to flick but the ball clips his thigh pad and goes fine down the leg side to the fence.
This one keeps low. It is on middle, Woakes though does well to defend it.
Fuller on off, Woakes pushes it through covers for a couple.
Bouncer! This one rises. It is away outside off, Woakes leaves it alone.
Fast inswinging ball on middle, Woakes tucks it with the swing towards square leg for one.
Off the pad. Flighted on middle and leg, Woakes looks to defend but the ball lobs up off his thigh pad towards short leg.
Shorter on the pads, Woakes looks to defend but once again it hits his thigh pad.
Turns it with the spin but finds square leg.
This time flicks it wide of square leg for a single.
Flighted outside off, Ali leaves it alone and there is a huge cheer from the crowd.
Outside off and once again Ali leaves it alone.
Pattinson sends this on the fourth stump line and the ball comes into the batsman as Woakes blocks it well.
FOUR! On the fourth stump line, Woakes leans forward and drives it past the gully fielder and the ball races to the fence.
Around off stump line on a good length, Woakes blocks it off his back foot.
Goes for a short ball but misses his line and strays way outside the leg stump. Woakes leaves it alone.
This on a good length on the fourth stump, Woakes lunges and blocks it towards off side.
Goes for a bouncer again, this is aimed at the body but does not rise as Woakes attempts a pull to get hit on the body.
Plays the sweep shot through square leg. The fielder in the deep runs to his right and then parries it to the fielder running to his left. He fumbles but only two taken.
Outside off, left alone.
Floats it up on off, this is kept out.
On middle this time, Moeen once again is solid in defense.
Gives it a little more air on middle, MA keeps it out.
That stays low! Flatter and on the pads, Ali gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
Pattinson bowls a short delivery, Woakes manages to keep it out.
On a good length on off, Woakes plays it to mid off.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Short of a length delivery, Woakes pulls it hard through mid-wicket for a boundary. The timing was so good on that.
FOUR! Consecutive boundaries for Chris Woakes. This is Chris Woakes' fifth boundary. Full on middle, Woakes flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary. This is excellent batting from him.
Good length delivery on off, Woakes defends it out.
FOUR! Poor delivery from James Pattinson. Bowls short and wide outside off, Woakes cuts it hard through point for a boundary. 12 runs have come from the over.
Floats it up on middle, Ali looks to defend but the ball turns away. It goes off the outer half to point.
Flatter and on middle, Moeen defends it.
Slower through the air outside off, Ali lets it be.
Another loopy ball just outside off, Ali lets it be.
On middle, Ali lunges and keeps it out.
Slightly shorter around middle, Ali pushes it back to the bowler.

That cut him in half! Terrific ball to start his new spell. Good length ball pitching outside off, it moves in sharply. Woakes looks to defend but the ball goes through the gate between pad and bat to the left of the keeper. Gem of a ball!
Length ball on off, Woakes drives it straight on the up, Siddles does well to get his hand on it and take the pace off. The ball goes wide of mid off and the batsmen take a run.
Length delivery outside off, Ali leaves it alone.

NOT OUT! Height is indeed the issue. Australia lose one of their two reviews. Length ball nipping in, Ali looks to defend but gets beaten. The ball hits him high on the pads. Australia ask the question but the umpire is not interested. Tim Paine signals the 'T'. Replays roll in and Hawk Eye shows that the ball was just over the leg stump.

Another appeal for LBW but once again it is turned down. This one comes back in too but once again hits high on the pad. Siddle puts a desperate appeal but nothing from the umpire. Australia do not take the review this time.
Fuller on off, Ali keeps it out to get through the over unscathed.
Flighted delivery on off, Woakes drives it to covers.
Tossed up on leg, Woakes pads it away.
Floated delivery on leg, Woakes again pads it away.
Tossed up on off, Woakes plays it to the off side.
Flighted delivery on off, Woakes keeps it out.
Full toss on leg, Woakes hits it to mid-wicket.
Full on off, Moeen pushes it to mid off.
On off, Moeen strokes it through covers and gets a couple.
Good ball and a good leave. It pitches outside off and comes in. Moeen though is aware of his off pole and leaves it alone.
Length delivery on off and middle, this is the one that moves away. Moeen does well to defend it. Ohhs and ahhs are the shout from the Aussie players.
IN THE AIR...BUT JUST WIDE! Fuller ball on off, Moeen drives it on the up. He does so uppishly as the ball sticks on the surface. Luckily it goes wide of Siddle's outstretched right hand to mid off.
On the fourth stump line, Moeen lets it carry to the keeper.
WOW! That is some delivery. It lands in the rough outside off. Woakes goes back and looks to defend but the ball turns back in sharply and hits the batsman high on the pad.
A little too full this time outside off, Woakes strokes it through covers for one.

OUT! TAKEN! Any guesses who gets Moeen Ali? It can't be that difficult for you to guess. I'll give you a hint, he has dismissed Moeen Ali 8 times in Tests before this one. Nathan Lyon it is. His fifth wicket. His 15th five-fer in Tests. It was him who Australia were going to rely on today and he delivers. Lyon tosses it up on middle, it pitches and turns away. Moeen Ali does not account for the turn. An outside edge which goes straight to Warner at second slip.

OUT! Caught at slip! A golden duck for Broad. Two wickets in two balls for Lyon. He has 6 now. Another left-hander falls prey to him. He floats it on off and gets this one to turn away too. Broad plays the original trajectory. The ball kisses the outside edge and this time Smith at first slip takes it. Australia a wicket away now and Lyon is on a hat-trick.
No hat-trick! A good solid block by Anderson. On middle, JA lunges and keeps it out.
BEAUTY! This lands on off and then turns away. Anderson looks to defend but is beaten. What an over from Lyon. 2 wickets and a run from it.
Good length ball outside off, Woakes has a poke at it but misses.
Fuller on off, Woakes pushes it to cover.
Length delivery just outside off, CW defends it to cover.
Pacy ball on the pads, Woakes looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Very full on off, Woakes does well to defend it to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Woakes taps it towards point and gets through the over. No chance of taking any quick run considering  Anderson's calf problem.
Flighted on off, Anderson does well to defend it.
Huge cheer from the crowd as Anderson blocks this one off his front foot.
The cheer continues as Anderson pushes this shot ball towards mid on.
Floated on off, Anderson does well to keep it out.
Tossed up on off, James blocks it out.
Anderson negotiates Lyon! Flatter on off, James defends it off the outer half of his bat towards backward point.
Length delivery outside off, Woakes has a push at it but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Woakes keeps it out of his back foot.
Woakes continues the battle. He defends it off the front foot.
Full on middle and off, Woakes defends it towards mid on.

DROPPED AND FOUR! Good length ball outside off, Woakes goes chasing after it. It takes the outside edge and goes to second slip. Smith, who has not put a foot wrong in this game, manages to make one error and drops the catch. The ball goes through him for a boundary.
Fuller on off, Woakes defends off his back foot but it goes off his outside edge and Smith dives to make a half-stop, Woakes takes a single to keep the strike.
Floated on the stumps, Woakes defends it off the front foot.
On the pads, CW turns it wide of short leg.
On the stumps, Chris keeps it out.
Short outside off, Woakes looks to cut but misses.
Woakes comes down the track and whips it to wide long on.
EDGED AND FOUR! Flighted on off, James looks to defend but the ball takes the fat outside edge of the bat and runs wide of first slip and to the third man fence for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Woakes pulls it to mid-wicket.
Bouncer! Woakes plays a no-look-pull but he plays it in a controlled manner towards backward square leg. They do not take the run.

OUT! Caught! That is it! Woakes' lone battle comes to an end! Cummins bangs one short, Woakes looks to leave but the ball is close to the body and he ends up playing it late. The ball lobs off the upper half of his bat towards second slip. Fittingly, the last catch is taken by Steve Smith! Australia win the first Ashes Test by 251 runs.
